Q7: Why is <label for="id"> important and why is placeholder not a replacement for it? Include two reasons — one about accessibility, one about UX.

Answer:
<label> is important because screen readers use it to identify form fields, improving accessibility.

<label> also improves user experience because clicking the label focuses the related input field.

Placeholder is not a replacement because it disappears when the user starts typing.
Labels remain visible and clearly identify the field.
